                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="Ethiopian false">
                                <decoNote xml:id="b1" type="bindingMaterial">
                                    The book is bound in <material key="wood">wooden</material> boards.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="Boards">
                                    The boards are flush with the bookblock and have square edges. The grain runs vertically.
                                    Both the external and inner surfaces of the boards are polished. On the external surface a finishing layer of dark colour has been added.
                                    The board attachment is uncommon. It only consists of two holes drilled through the thickness of the boards.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="SewingStations">3</decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b4">
                                    Chainstitch sewing on three sewing stations; continuous fold pattern; S-plied thread.
                                    The bookblock was probably sewn on four sewing stations and has been resewn on three, also substituting the boards. On the folios, the holes and the marks left by the previous sewing are present.
                                    The ends of the thread are knotted in the centrefold of the first quire.
                                    <locus target="#53"/> is stitched through the inner margin directly to <locus target="#54"/>.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b5" type="Spine">
                                    A piece of folded parchment protects the spine and is linked to the bookblock by stitching it to the holes for board attachment and the chains that the sewing forms on the spine.
                                    A yellow thread emerges from the tail edge of the bookblock.
                                </decoNote>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                        
